<plot>JUST A MINUTE is the 'dance' of a woman stuck in the rat race - she gets up, gets ready to go to work and tries to leave the house. The short celebrates the beauty of the mundane and explores the importance of reflection and pause in the 'rat race' of urban existence.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?282593</url></doc>
